It is no wonder that APIs, regardless of how much value they may deliver to customers, require high quality docs in order
to gain widespread adoption. In the past few years, two main styles of API documentation have dominated the industry. The
first and more popular style, of which the [Swagger UI](http://petstore.swagger.io/) is likely the best example of, lists
all the endpoints in your specification along with their low level functional details by category. The second major
